contentrichtext.text: '''Wasa''' may refer to any of the following: *[[Wasa Lake]], a place in British Columbia, Canada *[[Wasabröd]], a brandname used by the Swedish company AB Wasabröd *[[IK Wasa]], a big Swedish club *[[Vasa (ship)]], 17th-century Swedish warship, formerly spelled ''Wasa'' *SS ''Wasa'' (1907) a Swedish cargo ship launched in 1907, sold to Norway in 1925 and renamed [[SS Henry|SS ''Henry'']] *[[Vaasa]] or Vasa, a town in Finland with a large Swedish-speaking minority, formerly spelled ''Wasa'' *[[Wasa Line]], a former Finnish shipping company *[[Legion Wasa]], a Swedish political party *[[Wasa 30]], a Swedish sailboat *[[Wasa Amenfi West District]], a district in the Western Region of Ghana *[[Wasa language]], a variety of the Akan languages of Ghana and eastern Côte d'Ivoire *[[Wasa (Tanzanian ward)]], a Tanzanian ward in Iringa Rural district *[[Wasa, Cameroon]], a town in Extrême-Nord region '''WASA''' may refer to: *[[District of Columbia Water and Sewer Authority]] *[[Water and Sewerage Authority]] of Trinidad and Tobago *[[Water and Sanitation Agency]] of Pakistan *[[Western Action Shooting Association]] *[[Western Australia Softball Association]] ==See also== *''Wasa Wasa'', an album by [[Edgar Broughton Band]] *''Wasa'', an archaic spelling of the name of the Swedish [[House of Vasa|Royal House of Vasa]] *[[Vasa (disambiguation)]] {{disambig}} [[de:Vasa]]
